comment: Bluetooth LE advertising set callbacks, used to deliver advertising operation status.

variables.name: ADVERTISE_FAILED_DATA_TOO_LARGE
variables.comment: Failed to start advertising as the advertise data to be broadcasted is too large.

variables.name: ADVERTISE_FAILED_TOO_MANY_ADVERTISERS
variables.comment: Failed to start advertising because no advertising instance is available.

variables.name: ADVERTISE_FAILED_ALREADY_STARTED
variables.comment: Failed to start advertising as the advertising is already started.

variables.name: ADVERTISE_FAILED_INTERNAL_ERROR
variables.comment: Operation failed due to an internal error.

variables.name: ADVERTISE_FAILED_FEATURE_UNSUPPORTED
variables.comment: This feature is not supported on this platform.

methods.name: public void onAdvertisingSetStarted(AdvertisingSet advertisingSet, int txPower, int status)
methods.comment:
* Callback triggered in response to {@link BluetoothLeAdvertiser#startAdvertisingSet}
     * indicating result of the operation. If status is ADVERTISE_SUCCESS, then advertisingSet
     * contains the started set and it is advertising. If error occurred, advertisingSet is null,
     * and status will be set to proper error code.
     *
     * @param advertisingSet The advertising set that was started or null if error.
     * @param txPower tx power that will be used for this set.
     * @param status Status of the operation.

methods.name: public void onAdvertisingSetStopped(AdvertisingSet advertisingSet)
methods.comment:
* Callback triggered in response to {@link BluetoothLeAdvertiser#stopAdvertisingSet} indicating
     * advertising set is stopped.
     *
     * @param advertisingSet The advertising set.
